.TH "gsi_channel_poll" 9 "gsi_channel_poll" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gsi_channel_poll \- NAPI poll function for a channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gsi_channel_poll
.BI "(struct napi_struct *napi "  ","
.BI "int budget "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "napi" 12
NAPI structure for the channel
.IP "budget" 12
Budget supplied by NAPI core
.SH "RETURN"
Number of items polled (<= budget)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Single transactions completed by hardware are polled until either
the budget is exhausted, or there are no more.  Each transaction
polled is passed to \fBgsi_trans_complete\fP, to perform remaining
completion processing and retire/free the transaction.
